-------> STEWARDSHIP (10 min)

Stewardship describes the job of taking care of something valuable that we have been entrusted with

Each fellowship service we spend 10 minutes discussing stewardship as it relates to health and time/money

Health includes both our physical body and our mind


Within a Christian context, stewardship describes the responsibility that we have to maintain and wisely use the gifts that God has given us

This week we're talking about body stewardship and specifically, what God's word says about the food we eat

In the old testament God says "Every moving thing that lives shall be food for us in addition to plants with very explcicit instructions about exceptions regarding what we shouldn't eat


In the new testament, Jesus simplifies the question of what to eat and gives renwed guidance to replace the old testament restrictions around food

in Mark 7:18-19 Jesus says "Do you not see that whatever goes into a person from outside cannot defile him, since it enters not his heart, but his stomach and is expelled"?

So with those words, Jesus declared all foods clean. 

Jesus is saying that its not what goes into us that makes us unclean, but 



In 1 Timothy 4:4 Paul says "For everything created by God is good, and nothing is to be rejected if it is received by thanksgiving"

Paul is communicating the importance of giving thanks to the Lord for. I think what he says about things created by God being good also applies to food as a general principle about real food vs manufactured food products

My interpretation of that with food is that natural food is good. God didnt create fruit roll ups so they probebably arent good for us. He did create meat, papaya, and dates

Eat food made by God, not food products made by man




